# UI Page Guide — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> **What this is:** the page-by-page map of the frontend — every route → the data it shows → the
> endpoints/hooks that feed it → the DB objects behind them. The first stop for any UI or full-stack
> task: start here, not in the code.
>
> **Discipline:** [`scripts/check_doc_coverage.py`](scripts/check_doc_coverage.py) checks that **every
> live route** in `frontend/src/routeTree.gen.ts` has a row here. A live route missing from this guide
> is a **hard failure** at the pre-push gate; a route documented here but absent from code warns
> (phantom route — delete the row). Keep this honest as you add/rename/remove pages.

